                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.001 Vargas, Getulio/134: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-06T17:00:00-03:00"
                            >January 6, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. For the Under Secretary. Aranha<note n="93" xml:id="d601fn93">Oswaldo Aranha,
                        Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> tells me Martins<note n="94"
                        xml:id="d601fn94">Carlos Martins, Brazilian Ambassador in the United
                        States.</note> reports President Roosevelt told him to invite President
                    Vargas “to meet him at Trinidad” (when, not known).</p>
                <p>President Vargas says he will be glad to do it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
